spanishExample: Si me quedo, quiero sesenta y siete dólares.
englishTranslation: If I stay, I want sixty-seven dollars.

spanishExample: Tienes que quedarte donde nos quedamos.
englishTranslation: You have to stay where we stayed.

spanishExample: Quizás se quede.
englishTranslation: Maybe she’ll stay.

spanishExample: Me quedaré para que seamos setenta y siete y no setenta y seis.
englishTranslation: I’ll stay so that we’ll be seventy-seven and not seventy-six.

spanishExample: Quedaron setenta y cinco, no setenta y tres.
englishTranslation: There were seventy-five left, not seventy-three.

spanishExample: La ley dice que tenemos que quedarnos hasta que tengamos sesenta años.
englishTranslation: The law says we have to stay until we’re sixty.

spanishExample: Quédate y ayúdame con el sistema.
englishTranslation: Stay and help me with the system.

spanishExample: Te quedarás aquí porque yo me quedé aquí antes.
englishTranslation: You’ll stay here, because I stayed here before.

spanishExample: Tienen que quedar dos.
englishTranslation: There have to be two left.

spanishExample: Tengo derecho a quedarme.
englishTranslation: I have the right to stay.

spanishExample: No puede quedarse porque hay sesenta y una personas.
englishTranslation: He can’t stay because there are sixty-one people.

spanishExample: ¿Te quedas aquí hoy?
englishTranslation: Are you staying here today?

spanishExample: Quédese, ya hay como sesenta y nueve personas.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Stay, there are already like sixty-nine people.

spanishExample: Esto no me queda bien y vale sesenta y seis dólares.
englishTranslation: This doesn’t suit me and it’s worth sixty-six dollars.

spanishExample: Esto te puede quedar bien.
englishTranslation: This might suit you well.

spanishExample: Por favor quédense, no me gusta el silencio.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Please stay, I don’t like the silence.

spanishExample: No quedaba dinero, aunque habíamos tenido setenta y cuatro dólares.
englishTranslation: No money was left, even though we had had seventy-four dollars.

spanishExample: No nos quedamos, pero ella se quedó.
englishTranslation: We didn’t stay, but she stayed.

spanishExample: Quedaba un modo de hacer eso.
englishTranslation: There was one mode left to do that.

spanishExample: Yo era el único que quedaba.
englishTranslation: I was the only person that was left.

spanishExample: Esto te quedará bien en un mes.
englishTranslation: This will suit you well in a month.

spanishExample: Se han quedado en ese hotel antes.
englishTranslation: They have stayed in that hotel before.

spanishExample: Solo quedan setenta dólares.
englishTranslation: There are only seventy dollars left.

spanishExample: ¡Que lo pases bien con tu libertad!
englishTranslation: May you have a good time with your freedom!

spanishExample: No te quedes aquí, quiero que te quedes ahí.
englishTranslation: Don’t stay here, I want you to stay there.

spanishExample: ¡Que te quede bien!
englishTranslation: May it suit you well!

spanishExample: No creo que quede nada.
englishTranslation: I don’t think there’s anything left.
